description:
Create Sidekiq job(s) that will use the Jira interface created in https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/issues/208910 and the serializer created in https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/issues/208911 to create GitLab issues from those in a JIRA Project.

- 100% of issues in the JIRA project should be recreated on GitLab;
- GitLab issue author should be the user that initiated the import job;
- If metadata is not included in the description in #209792 it should be added as a comment to the created issue:
  - e.g. `This issue was imported from JIRA on 2020-03-04 by @johnhope`;
- Job should update the state of the object created in #208907 when commenced, and
- Job should update the state of the object created in #208907 when complete.

@jprovaznik 's [comment](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/merge_requests/23406#note_297886465):

> I wonder if we could decrease complexity from 10 to e.g. 5 when this optimization is turned on by default? :thinking:

We can re-evaluate once we have an idea of how expensive getting epic count and weight sum aggregates becomes in production.
